The paper deals with the problem of signal classification and receiver design for non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) in the context of Internet of Things (IoT) networks. This involves issues related to information theory (cs.IT), networking (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
